 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Assassination Rogue Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 169 top-ranked Assassination Rogue DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Assassination Rogue items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Edgewalker Longboots (89%), Deathmantle Handguards (81%), Drape of the Dark Reavers (79%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should an Assassination Rogue use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Rigid Dawnstone, Glinting Noble Topaz and Shifting Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does an Assassination Rogue need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "9 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Greater Inscription of Vengeance on shoulders, Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Mongoose on weapon. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
